The course examines the system, general principles and basic institutes of the company law, legal regulation of different types of companies and partnerships in Estonian and EU law, reorganization of companies and other matters connected to toe company law (branch office, groups of companies).Objectives/eesmärkid:  General objectives of the subject are to teach basic knowledge of the company law, to explain development of company law, connection of the company law with the other institutes of law and to give a theoretical and practical knowledge for solving the company law cases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course the student have to be capable: - to know the basic institutes of company law and to connect them with the other fields of law - to explain the objectives of the company law norms and principles - to understand the basis of the application of the norms and principles of the company law to apply them - to recognize the legal problems solved by the norms and principles of the company law - to have a knowledge in the important company law court cases - to solve independently company law cases according to the applicable methodology
